Instance creation


Oracle Firewall setup

 Instances-> Security->Security list (click the created security list as "Default Security List for openvpn-905" in my case) ->Security Rules (Ingress and Egress)

 make changes as image oracle-8 and oracle-9

Also Open Network Security Group


Instances-> Security->Network Security Groups (click the created list as "ig-quick-action-NSG" in my case)

 make changes as image oracle-10



SSH key 

generate SSH key pair on your local PC 


ls ~/.ssh   
You should see something like:

id_rsa   //private key
id_rsa.pub   //public key


File	Used Where
id_rsa.pub	goes INTO server
id_rsa	goes INTO GitHub secret


Open private key:

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa

It MUST look like:

-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
...
-----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----

or

-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
...
-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----


Add Public Key to Oracle VM
login using SSH

on oracle VN terminal
mkdir -p ~/.ssh
nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

Paste contents of:

~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

Save and fix permissions:

chmod 700 ~/.ssh
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys


Put PRIVATE Key in GitHub Secret

Go to:

Repo → Settings → Secrets → Actions → SSH_KEY

Delete old value.

Paste FULL private key, including:

-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
...
-----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----